# Sūra LXXXVIII.: <u>G</u>āshiya, or The Overwhelming Event.

### Section 1

![](../gif/088/088_001.gif)

1. Hal at<u>a</u>ka <u>h</u>adeethu algh<u>a</u>shiyat**i**

1\. Has the story  
Reached thee, of  
The Overwhelming (Event)?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_002.gif)

2. Wujoohun yawma-i<u>th</u>in kh<u>a</u>shiAAa**tun**

2\. Some faces, that Day,  
Will be humiliated,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_003.gif)

3. AA<u>a</u>milatun n<u>as</u>iba**tun**

3\. Labouring (hard), weary,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_004.gif)

4. Ta<u>s</u>l<u>a</u> n<u>a</u>ran <u>ha</u>miya**tan**

4\. The while they enter  
The Blazing Fire,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_005.gif)

5. Tusq<u>a</u> min AAaynin <u>a</u>niya**tin**

5\. The while they are given,  
To drink, of a bailing hot spring,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_006.gif)

6. Laysa lahum <u>t</u>aAA<u>a</u>mun ill<u>a</u> min
<u>d</u>areeAA**in**

6\. No food will there be  
For them but a bitter <u>Dh</u>arī’

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_007.gif)

7. L<u>a</u> yusminu wal<u>a</u> yughnee min jooAA**in**

7\. Which will neither nourish  
Nor satisfy hunger.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_008.gif)

8. Wujoohun yawma-i<u>th</u>in n<u>a</u>AAima**tun**

8\. (Other) faces that Day  
Will be joyful,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_009.gif)

9. LisaAAyih<u>a</u> r<u>ad</u>iya**tun**

9\. Pleased with their Striving,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_010.gif)

10. Fee jannatin AA<u>a</u>liya**tin**

10\. In a Garden on high,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_011.gif)

11. L<u>a</u> tasmaAAu feeh<u>a</u> l<u>a</u>ghiya**tan**

11\. Where they shall hear  
No (word) of vanity:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_012.gif)

12. Feeh<u>a</u> AAaynun j<u>a</u>riya**tun**

12\. Therein will be  
A bubbling spring:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_013.gif)

13. Feeh<u>a</u> sururun marfooAAa**tun**

13\. Therein will be Thrones  
(Of dignity), raised on high,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_014.gif)

14. Waakw<u>a</u>bun maw<u>d</u>ooAAa**tun**

14\. Goblets placed (ready),

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_015.gif)

15. Wanam<u>a</u>riqu ma<u>s</u>foofa**tun**

15\. And Cushions set in rows,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_016.gif)

16. Wazar<u>a</u>biyyu mabthootha**tun**

16\. And rich carpets  
(All) spread out.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_017.gif)

17. Afal<u>a</u> yan*<u>th</u>*uroona il<u>a</u> al-ibili kayfa khuliqat

17\. Do they not look  
At the Camels,  
How they are made?—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_018.gif)

18. Wa-il<u>a</u> a**l**ssam<u>a</u>-i kayfa rufiAAat

18\. And at the Sky,  
How it is raised high?—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_019.gif)

19. Wa-il<u>a</u> aljib<u>a</u>li kayfa nu<u>s</u>ibat

19\. And at the Mountains,  
How they are fixed firm?—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_020.gif)

20. Wa-il<u>a</u> al-ar<u>d</u>i kayfa su<u>t</u>i<u>h</u>at

20\. And at the Earth,  
How it is spread out?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_021.gif)

21. Fa<u>th</u>akkir innam<u>a</u> anta mu<u>th</u>akkir**un**

21\. Wherefore do thou give  
Admonition, for thou art  
One to admonish.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_022.gif)

22. Lasta AAalayhim bimu<u>s</u>ay<u>t</u>ir**in**

22\. Thou art not one  
To manage (men's) affairs.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_023.gif)

23. Ill<u>a</u> man tawall<u>a</u> wakafar**a**

23\. But if any turn away  
And reject God,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_024.gif)

24. FayuAAa<u>thth</u>ibuhu All<u>a</u>hu alAAa<u>tha</u>ba
al-akbar**a**

24\. God will punish him  
With a mighty Punishment,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_025.gif)

25. Inna ilayn<u>a</u> iy<u>a</u>bahum

25\. For to Us will be  
Their Return;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/088/088_026.gif)

26. Thumma inna AAalayn<u>a</u> <u>h</u>is<u>a</u>bahum

26\. Then it will be for Us  
To call them to account.

